(143, 142, 1, 1, 'bledixhindi', 'Homeless problem', '<p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: medium;\">The big problem is homeless people. The many problems they have such as not having food, not being educated, not having a family. These problems can be solved if the state takes some actions.Some of the ways a state can reduce the number of homeless people are training for work, income donation, education, however small, and giving a second chance.If a homeless person is trained to do a certain job and he applies for that job he will have enough money to live on. If he goes well he can start a family and so he will be a happy and not homeless man.The ways that homeless people can be helped by the state are numerous but not many countries do this and the number of homeless people grows and grows. Therefore, the state must intervene and regulate these situations that people are in.All the various associations that help the homeless should work closely with the state to make this problem a story and not a daily act.Over 60 % of the countries in the world have this kind of basic problem, not only the small states but also the superpowers have more serious problems on this topic. Although a strong state still fails to systematize this situation.This problem must be solved as soon as possible.</span></p>', '185.89.159.80', 1633869903, 0),
